sfReplaceAttribute

public java.lang.Object sfReplaceAttribute(java.lang.Object name,
                                           java.lang.Object value)
                                    throws SmartFrogRuntimeException,
                                           java.rmi.RemoteException
Description copied from class: CompoundImpl
Replace named attribute in component context. If attribute is not present it is added to the context. If the attribute value added is a component description, then its parent is set to this and/or if the one removed is a component description then its parent is reset. If the attribute is defined as requiring injection - the attribute will be injected after the value of the attribute has been set. This methods rejects a double registration of an existing child.

Specified by:
sfReplaceAttribute in interface Prim
Overrides:
sfReplaceAttribute in class CompoundImpl
Parameters:
name - of attribute to replace
value - value to add or replace
Returns:
the old value if present, null otherwise. It old value was a component description, then its prim parent is reset.
Throws:
SmartFrogRuntimeException - when name or value are null, or injection failed
java.rmi.RemoteException - In case of Remote/network error
